&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Title: Academy Director &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Joint role for Herefordshire &amp; Worcestershire STP and Worcestershire Acute Hospitals NHS Trust)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours: Up to 37.5 per week (minimum of 22.5 hours)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band:8d&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced and well organised individual to undertake the newly created role of Academy Director. The role will be responsible for the development of a “one stop shop” for all education, learning and development needs at both Sustainability and Transformation Partnership (STP) level and for Worcestershire Acute Hospitals NHS Trust. This will include establishing faculties for each of the health and care staff groups ensuring each faculty has defined career pathways and frameworks for mandatory training, essential to role training, continued professional development and personal development for relevant staff groups.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have worked in a senior education, learning and development role within education, health and/or social care and have a strong track record in multi-organisational stakeholder and relationship management; have demonstrable experience of successfully delivering complex and innovative education, learning and development and have an excellent knowledge of the current health and care, people and culture challenges. You will need to be able to motivate and influence at all levels and demonstrate excellent communication and organisational skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we offer a unique opportunity to work across our ambitious and diverse STP with the freedom to work flexibility to achieve our goals. You will be well supported by the STP Executive Workforce Director and other established leaders across the system but will have significant personal and professional discretion to demonstrate your leadership skills and further potential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be hosted by Worcestershire Acute Hospitals NHS Trust on behalf of the STP and will be expected to undertake work flexibly to suit the needs of the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information regarding the position please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tina Ricketts &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;STP Executive Workforce Director &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;01905 760808&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;tina.ricketts@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
